# SASS Installation Steps

## Method 1: Using Node.js and npm (Recommended)

1. Install Node.js version 20.16.0 using nvm:

   ```bash
   curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash
   ```

2. Exit and reopen terminal to load nvm

3. Install and use Node.js v20.16.0:

   ```bash
   nvm install 20.16.0
   nvm use 20.16.0
   ```

4. Install SASS globally:

   ```bash
   npm install -g sass@3.7.4
   ```

## Method 2: Alternative installation (if Node.js is already installed)

1. Install SASS using npm:

   ```bash
   npm install sass -v 3.7.4
   ```

## Verification

Check if SASS is installed correctly:

```bash
sass --version
```

## Note for Windows Users

- Ensure PowerShell execution policy allows scripts
- Consider using Git Bash or WSL for better compatibility with Unix commands
- You may need to use `npm install -g sass` instead of the version-specific command
